ar.%20The%20latest%20in%20the%20series%20of%20issues%20is%20of%20a%20security%20bug%20where%20Aadhaar-based%20KYC%20(know%20your%20customer)%20details%20of%20every%20company%20director%2C%20including%20industrialists%20and%20celebrities%20like%20Ratan%20Tata%2C%20Mukesh%20Ambani%2C%20Gautam%20Adani%2C%20Virat%20Kohli%2C%20and%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%2C%20were%20accessible%20without%20authorisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecurity%20researcher%20Sai%20Krishna%20Kothapalli%20of%20Hackcrew%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkmskrishna.me%2Fhow-the-personal-data-of-indias-richest-could-have-been-leaked-1952207d9fcd%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealing%20details%20of%20the%20security%20issue.%20The%20report%20disclosed%20how%20the%20issue%20was%20fixed%20only%20after%2011%20months%2C%20after%20it%20was%20reported%20to%20the%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20(CERT-In).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo-300x209.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo-300x209.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-637305%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22209%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20related%20to%20any%20company%20activity%20is%20made%20available%20to%20the%20general%20public%20for%20carrying%20out%20business%20transactions%20and%20verification%2C%20as%20part%20of%20market%20activities.%20The%20MCA%20portal%20performs%20an%20important%20function%20in%20this%20regard.%20It%20disseminates%20this%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Companies%20Act%20and%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%2C%20KYC%20norms%20exist%20to%20stop%20operations%20of%20shell%20companies%20involved%20in%20any%20illegal%20activities.%20A%20part%20of%20this%20KYC%20information%20is%20shared%20publicly%20to%20anyone%20who%20wants%20to%20verify%20details%20of%20the%20company%20or%20the%20director%2C%20with%20whom%20they%20are%20entering%20into%20a%20business%20contract%20under%20the%20Companies%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20security%20report%20details%20how%20the%20personal%20information%20that%20was%20available%20to%20be%20accessible%20on%20the%20MCA%20portal%20was%20much%20more%20than%20what%20is%20published%20by%20MCA.%20The%20data%20model%20shared%20in%20the%20report%20shows%20personal%20details%2C%20such%20as%20Aadhaar%20number%2C%20permanent%20account%20number%20(PAN)%2C%20Voter%20ID%2C%20address%2C%20mobile%20number%2C%20and%20email%20ID.%20The%20data%20model%20includes%20internal%20flags%20designated%20by%20MCA%2C%20such%20as%20company%20director%20status%2C%20and%20whether%20director%20address%20is%20shared%20with%20another%20director%20to%20look%20for%20ghost%20directors%20and%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20387px)%2085vw%2C%20387px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17145440%2Fimage-1750.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22387%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17145440%2Fimage-1750.png%20387w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17145440%2Fimage-1750-169x300.png%20169w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693334%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22687%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERedacted%20data%20model%20that%20has%20personal%20details%20of%20Ratan%20Tata.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20shows%20yet%20again%20how%20Aadhaar%20data%20that%20is%20being%20collected%20as%20part%20of%20the%20KYC%20process%20is%20often%20leaky%20because%20the%20institutions%20that%20collect%20it%20don%E2%80%99t%20safeguard%20this%20data.%20The%20institutions%20that%20are%20responsible%20for%20quality%20checks%20and%20security%20audits%20are%20Software%20Testing%20and%20Quality%20Certification%20(STQC)%20and%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20(CERT-In).%20Both%20of%20them%20have%20continued%20to%20fail%20in%20responding%20to%20these%20issues.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Aadhaar%2C%20its%20regulator%20Unique%20Identification%20Authority%20of%20India%20(UIDAI)%20has%20also%20consistently%20failed%20in%20regulating%20institutions%20that%20have%20leaked%20any%20Aadhaar%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findians-personal-data-breached-yet-again-but-no-sign-that-gaps-will-be-plugged%5C%22%3EIndians%E2%80%99%20Personal%20Data%20Breached%20Yet%20Again%2C%20but%20No%20Sign%20That%20Gaps%20Will%20Be%20Plugged%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20CERT-In%20has%20to%20respond%20to%20all%20security%20vulnerabilities%20disclosed%20to%20them%20and%20immediately%20address%20them.%20Certain%20security%20vulnerabilities%20are%20hard%20to%20fix%20overnight%20and%20do%20require%20time%20to%20issue%20security%20patches%20to%20fix%20them.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20CERT-In%20was%20informed%20about%20the%20security%20issue%20in%20January%202023.%20While%20it%20flagged%20the%20issue%2C%20it%20did%20not%20fix%20it%20immediately.%20Even%20now%2C%20whether%20the%20issue%20is%20completely%20fixed%20is%20unknown%2C%20as%20CERT-In%20does%20not%20conduct%20any%20forensic%20analysis%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20the%20issue%20to%20continue%20to%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20the%20security%20researcher%2011%20months%2C%20from%20January%20to%20December%202023%2C%20to%20analyse%20this%20process.%20The%20analysis%20also%20indicates%20a%20lack%20of%20capacity%20within%20CERT-IN%20to%20address%20such%20issues%2C%20even%20when%20they%20are%20reported%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20security%20bug%20is%20a%20software%20bug%20that%20has%20been%20introduced%20because%20of%20poor%20software%20programming%20and%20quality%20control.%20Company%20secretaries%20and%20chartered%20accountants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fbusiness%2Fchartered-accountants-flag-concerns-about-glitches-in-mca-21-portal-16462311.htm%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20criticising%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20MCA%20portal%20over%20how%20the%20portal%20has%20several%20software%20issues%20and%20does%20not%20really%20work.%20However%2C%20a%20security%20issue%2C%20couple%20with%20all%20these%20other%20issues%2C%20does%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20The%20lack%20of%20institutional%20accountability%20in%20this%20process%20continues%20to%20show%20how%20no%20one%20inside%20the%20government%20takes%20issues%20related%20to%20software%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20economic%20nature%20of%20this%20information%2C%20several%20companies%20and%20data%20providers%20collect%20this%20information%20and%20are%20already%20providing%20economic%20services%20on%20top%20of%20this%20information.%20There%20is%20an%20entire%20ecosystem%20of%20companies%20that%20provides%20business%20alerts%20and%20changes%20on%20company%20data%20as%20products%20to%20market%20actors%2C%20such%20as%20venture%20capitalists%2C%20investors%2C%20banks%2C%20news%20agencies%2C%20and%20other%20competitors.%20While%20there%20are%20companies%20which%20only%20provide%20information%20that%20is%20publicly%20being%20shared%20by%20the%20MCA%2C%20there%20are%20other%20entities%20which%20share%20the%20personal%20details%20of%20directors%2C%20such%20as%20their%20phone%20numbers%20and%20email%20IDs%2C%20as%20an%20extra%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20organisations%20or%20data%20brokers%20may%20have%20already%20obtained%20part%20or%20full%20information%20of%20these%20companies%20and%20directors%20through%20security%20bugs%20in%20the%20MCA%20portal.%20The%20MCA%20website%20only%20publishes%20basic%20information%20publicly%20when%20any%20user%20wants%20to%20verify%20the%20director%20identification%20number%20or%20their%20PAN.%20This%20is%20not%20excessive%20information%20and%20the%20Companies%20Act%20mandates%20this%20information%20to%20be%20public.%20The%20problem%20is%20with%20the%20additional%20information%2C%20such%20as%20Aadhaar%2C%20PAN%2C%20mobile%20numbers%2C%20and%20email%20ID%2C%20which%20is%20typically%20not%20provided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17150716%2Fmca.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221004%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17150716%2Fmca.png%201004w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F17150716%2Fmca-300x167.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693340%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22559%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERatan%20Tata%E2%80%99s%20director%20identification%20number%20on%20the%20MCA%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELarge%20organisations%2C%20such%20as%20government%20departments%2C%20collect%20information%20for%20a%20range%20of%20regulatory%20activities%20and%20are%20often%20legally%20required%20to%20do%20so.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20ministry%20has%20to%20collect%20information%20for%20various%20compliance%20activities%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20is%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20control%20the%20flow%20of%20information%2C%20which%20is%20unacceptable.%20Policies%20like%20the%20National%20Data%20Sharing%20and%20Accessibility%20Policy%20mandate%20government%20departments%20to%20classify%20their%20datasets%20into%20open%2C%20shareable%2C%20and%20restricted%20categories%20to%20ensure%20the%20proper%20management%20of%20data%20flow.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20activity%20has%20largely%20been%20ignored%20by%20government%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdeanonymisation-in-non-personal-data%5C%22%3EWithout%20a%20Data%20Privacy%20Law%2C%20India%20Must%20Consider%20Hazards%20of%20%E2%80%98Deanonymisation%E2%80%99%20of%20Non-Personal%20Data%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%202023%2C%20which%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20enforced%2C%20completely%20exempts%20government%20departments.%20Despite%20this%20exemption%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20government%20still%20has%20to%20do%20a%20forensic%20analysis%20to%20identify%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20data%20leak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20has%20announced%20a%20draft%20national%20data%20governance%20policy%2C%20in%20which%20an%20India%20Data%20Management%20Office%20was%20supposed%20to%20classify%20various%20datasets%20with%20the%20government.%20However%2C%20this%20office%20has%20not%20been%20set%20up%20yet%2C%20and%20the%20process%20is%20still%20underway.%20Until%20this%20classification%20takes%20place%2C%20these%20issues%20will%20likely%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20it%20was%20Ratan%20Tata%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fnews-archive%2Fweb%2F2g-tapes-my-privacy-violated-tata-tells-sc%2F%5C%22%3Eapproached%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20demanding%20privacy%20regulation%20after%20his%20telephonic%20conversations%20were%20leaked%20as%20part%20of%20the%202G%20scam%20in%202010.%20Even%20after%20many%20years%2C%20the%20state%20is%20still%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20enforce%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fskodali%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ESrinivas%20Kodali%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20is%20a%20researcher%20on%20digitisation