%20up%20with%20the%20winning%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETsunami%20versus%20glacier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20numerous%20efforts%20to%20forecast%20its%20moves%2C%20the%20real-estate%20industry%20is%20wildly%20unpredictable%3B%20good%20luck%20guessing%20where%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20be%20in%2010%20years%20or%20how%20many%20new%20homes%20will%20hit%20the%20market.%20Demographic%20patterns%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20follow%20a%20more%20certain%20path%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20estimate%20when%20generations%20will%20start%20to%20fade%20away.%20Historical%20data%20tells%20us%20we%20can%20expect%20boomers%20to%20begin%20aging%20out%20of%20their%20homes%20after%20they%20reach%2080%2C%20Odeta%20Kushi%2C%20the%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20for%20the%20title%20company%20First%20American%2C%20told%20me.%20Given%20that%20boomers%20are%20currently%20between%2060%20and%2078%2C%20Kushi%20said%2C%20we%20should%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20boomers%20leaving%20their%20homes%20around%202030.%20Gary%20Engelhardt%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20Syracuse%20University%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20fate%20of%20boomers'%20homes%2C%20told%20me%20he%20expects%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20boomer%20generation%20to%20age%20out%20of%20the%20market%20between%202030%20and%202040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20next%2015%20years%2C%20this%20stuff's%20really%20going%20to%20start%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Engelhardt%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20homes%20hang%20in%20the%20balance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-greed-ruined-economy-gen-z-millennials-labor-shortage-inflation-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoomers%20claimed%2041.6%25%20of%20the%20real-estate%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%20as%20of%20the%20third%20quarter%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Census%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%20As%20of%202022%2C%20a%20whopping%2079%25%20of%20baby%20boomers%20owned%20the%20homes%20they%20lived%20in%2C%20compared%20with%2052%25%20of%20millennials%20and%20more%20than%2026%25%20of%20adult%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20per%20a%20Redfin%20analysis%20of%20Census%20data.%20In%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fresearch%2Fsilver-tsunami-inventory-boomers-24933%2F%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EZillow%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20nation's%20owner-occupied%20homes%2C%20or%20more%20than%2020%20million%20units%2C%20would%20hit%20the%20market%20over%20the%20following%20two%20decades%20as%20a%20result%20of%20boomers%20aging.%20The%20report%2C%20written%20by%20Issi%20Romem%2C%20called%20this%20wave%20of%20homes%20the%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20tsunami%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bboost%20the%20supply%20of%20housing%20on%20a%20magnitude%20comparable%20to%20the%20fluctuations%20that%20new%20home%20construction%20experienced%20in%20the%202000s%20boom-bust%20cycle.%26quot%3B%20The%20Wall%20Street%20forecaster%20Meredith%20Whitney%2C%20known%20for%20calling%20the%202008%20housing%20crash%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-mortgage-home-prices-supply-boomers-2008-crash-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresurfaced%20the%20silver-tsunami%20theory%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20predicting%20that%20the%20influx%20of%20housing%20inventory%20from%20widespread%20aging%20would%20lower%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Engelhardt%20and%20other%20economists%20told%20me%20the%20long-awaited%20boomer%20sell-off%20would%20likely%20take%20longer%20and%20wreak%20far%20less%20havoc%20than%20the%20tsunami%20metaphor%20would%20suggest.%20In%20his%202022%20paper%2C%20%26quot%3BWho%20will%20buy%20the%20baby%20boomers'%20homes%20when%20they%20leave%20them%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20Engelhardt%20argued%20that%20mass%20aging%20would%20send%20ripples%20through%20the%20housing%20market%20but%20fail%20to%20push%20down%20prices%20significantly.%20Because%20aging%20is%20predictable%20and%20takes%20time%2C%20Engelhardt%20told%20me%2C%20markets%20will%20adjust%20to%20any%20spike%20in%20available%20homes.%20If%20there%20are%20more%20homes%20for%20sale%20than%20the%20market%20can%20absorb%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20excess%20supply%2C%20many%20would-be%20sellers%20may%20start%20turning%20units%20into%20rentals%2C%20which%20would%20prevent%20prices%20from%20dropping%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20allow%20these%20conversions%2C%20where%20basically%20you%20could%20take%20a%20house%20that%20would%20typically%20be%20used%20by%20an%20older%20family%20and%20now%20it's%20available%20to%20a%20younger%20family%20as%20a%20rental%2C%26quot%3B%20Engelhardt%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20that%20is%20kind%20of%20an%20escape%20valve%2C%20a%20pressure%20release.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Engelhardt's%20model%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20likened%20to%20a%20glacier%20rather%20than%20a%20tsunami%20%E2%80%94%20the%20great%20boomer%20exit%20will%20contribute%20to%20an%20excess%20supply%20of%20about%20250%2C000%20homes%20a%20year%20until%20about%202032.%20After%20that%20point%2C%20demand%20for%20home%20purchases%20will%20once%20again%20outpace%20supply%20as%20millennials%20buy%20more%20homes%20and%20younger%20generations%2C%20like%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Gen%20Alpha%2C%20file%20in%20behind%20them.%20A%20quarter%20of%20a%20million%20homes%20annually%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20houses%2C%20but%20it's%20%26quot%3Ba%20drop%20in%20the%20bucket%2C%26quot%3B%20Engelhardt%20said.%20For%20reference%2C%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20said%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fnewsroom%2Fexisting-home-sales-expanded-0-8-in-november-ending-five-month-slide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esales%20of%20existing%20homes%20in%202023%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20on%20pace%20to%20reach%203.8%20million%20as%20of%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoomers'%20departure%20may%20not%20lead%20to%20a%20housing-market%20free-for-all%2C%20but%20their%20homes%20will%20have%20to%20go%20to%20somebody.%20And%20in%20the%20power%20vacuum%20left%20behind%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20%E2%80%94%20not%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20have%20the%20brightest%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGen%20Z%20on%20top%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%2C%20born%20between%201981%20and%201996%2C%20have%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-house-home-real-estate-mortgage-rates-rent-debt-boomers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epretty%20rough%20go%20in%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20started%20their%20careers%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20took%20on%20far%20more%20student%20debt%20than%20their%20predecessors%20did%2C%20and%20were%20left%20to%20contend%20with%20a%20housing%20crunch%20caused%20by%20a%20slowdown%20in%20homebuilding.%20They%20faced%20competition%20not%20just%20from%20their%20peers%20but%20from%20baby%20boomers%2C%20who've%20been%20far%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-versus-millennials-housing-war-competition-buying-home-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eactive%20buyers%20later%20in%20life%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20previous%20generations%20were.%20Left%20to%20dream%20of%20better%20days%20ahead%2C%20millennials%20have%20hoped%20that%20boomers'%20eventual%20exit%20will%20unleash%20an%20onslaught%20of%20vacant%20homes%20and%20lower%20prices%20enough%20for%20them%20to%20hop%20on%20the%20ladder.%20But%20once%20again%2C%20the%20timing%20looks%20like%20it%20won't%20work%20out%20in%20their%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20that%20millennials%20will%20be%20that%20generation%20who%20benefits%26quot%3B%20from%20boomers'%20departure%2C%20Jessica%20Lautz%2C%20the%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20at%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%2C%20told%20me.%20With%20the%20oldest%20millennials%20in%20their%2040s%2C%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20generation%20will%20have%20already%20purchased%20their%20first%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20stretching%20their%20budgets%20in%20the%20process%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20when%20boomers'%20houses%20finally%20become%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20all%20hope%20is%20lost%20for%20millennials.%20As%20boomers%20really%20start%20to%20sell%20off%20their%20homes%20or%20downsize%2C%20the%20lucky%20millennials%20who've%20already%20bought%20a%20home%20will%20be%20thinking%20about%20moving%20into%20bigger%20places%20for%20their%20growing%20families.%20Many%20of%20these%20boomer%20houses%20will%20be%20in%20prime%20locations%20in%20cities%20like%20New%20York%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Chicago%2C%20and%20Dallas%2C%20Kushi%20told%20me.%20But%20millennials%20looking%20to%20gain%20a%20foothold%20in%20the%20market%20will%20have%20missed%20out%20on%20years%20of%20wealth%20building%20by%20that%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20boomers%20eventually%20leave%20their%20homes%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20going%20to%20see%20more%20existing-home%20inventory%20opening%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%20Bachaud%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Zillow%2C%20told%20me%20in%202022%20when%20I%20began%20writing%20about%20the%20gloomy%20outlook%20for%20millennials.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20a%20long%20time%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20winners%20in%20all%20this%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-is-the-luckiest-generation-vs-millennials%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They've%20already%20gotten%20off%20to%20a%20stronger%20start%20on%20their%20homebuying%20journeys%20than%20previous%20generations%20did%3A%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fnews%2Fgen-z-millennial-homeownership-rate-home-purchases%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanalysis%20from%20Redfin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2030%25%20of%2025-year-olds%20owned%20their%20home%20in%202022%2C%20compared%20with%20a%2027%25%20rate%20for%20Gen%20Xers%20at%20the%20same%20point%20in%20their%20lives.%20(Millennials%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20were%20still%20struggling%20to%20match%20their%20parents%3A%20Redfin%20found%20that%2062%25%20of%2040-year-olds%20owned%20their%20home%20in%202022%2C%20down%20from%20a%2069%25%20rate%20for%20boomers%20at%20the%20same%20age.)%20The%20oldest%20Gen%20Zers%20will%20be%20in%20their%2030s%20in%202030%2C%20within%20the%20prime%20years%20for%20first-time%20buyers%2C%20Kushi%20told%20me.%20The%20Gen%20Z%20cohort%20is%20smaller%20than%20the%20millennial%20group%20and%20won't%20face%20as%20much%20competition%20from%20boomers%2C%20meaning%20they'll%20probably%20face%20less%20pressure%20in%20the%20market%20than%20the%20generation%20before%20them.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.firstam.com%2Feconomics%2Fwhen-boomers-and-millennials-collide-tectonic-shifts-in-demographics-are-coming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%20from%20First%20American%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20the%20reduced%20demand%20could%20help%20narrow%20the%20housing%20shortage%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%20The%20timing%20of%20boomers'%20exit%20will%20mostly%20benefit%20younger%20generations%2C%20like%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Gen%20Alpha%2C%20who%20should%20find%20themselves%20on%20steadier%20footing%20than%20their%20predecessors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20silver%20bullet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoomers'%20passing%20won't%20have%20a%20simple%20trickle-down%20effect.%20Not%20all%20members%20of%20subsequent%20generations%20will%20want%20to%20live%20where%20baby%20boomers%20have%20settled%20down%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20homes%20will%20require%20updates%20to%20appeal%20to%20younger%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20dwellings%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20considered%20adequate%2C%20will%20still%20likely%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Kushi%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoomers'%20mere%20absence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-baby-boomers-stop-complaining-wealth-housing-economy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewon't%20signal%20the%20end%20of%20the%20housing%20crunch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20either%2C%20Lautz%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20we%20have%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20boomers%20as%20a%20solution%20to%20the%20housing%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%20building%20and%20building%20more%20affordable%20inventory.%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20the%20silver%20bullet%20is%20waiting%20for%20baby%20boomers%20to%20need%20a%20smaller%20property%2C%20move%20in%20with%20family%2C%20or%20move%20into%20a%20senior%20center.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInevitably%2C%20though%2C%20baby%20boomers%20will%20hand%20over%20the%20reins%20to%20the%20generations%20behind%20them.%20Demographic%20projections%20give%20us%20a%20pretty%20good%20idea%20of%20when%20this%20shift%20will%20happen%20and%20who%20will%20be%20best%20positioned%20to%20end%20up%20ahead%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20The%20timing%20may%20not%20favor%20downtrodden%20millennials%2C%20but%20things%20are%20looking%20up%20for%20their%20luckier%2C%20savvier%20younger%20siblings.%20Zoomers%2C%20rejoice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-will-happen-baby-boomer-homes-die-millennials-gen-z-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E