345459_2a34eacff103c9cb52b3b8df13519eb0810a0f1d0_0_2736_18241000x667.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67999465%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Islamabad%20condemns%20%26quot%3Billegal%26quot%3B%20attack%2C%20which%20comes%20after%20Iranian%20strikes%20on%20targets%20in%20Syria%20and%20Iraq.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A140%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67999465%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67999465.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67999465.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Biden%20administration%20wants%20to%20save%20Americans%20%243.5%20billion%20a%20year%20by%20making%20sure%20banks%20aren't%20profiting%20too%20much%20off%20of%20overdraft%20fees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rohit%20Chopra%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b6d18d1ccd1e00198aa9ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222756%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERohit%20Chopra%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20(CFPB)%2C%20speaks%20during%20a%20Senate%20Banking%2C%20Housing%2C%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20Committee%20hearing%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20US%2C%20on%20June%2013%2C%202023.%20The%20committee%20held%20a%20hearing%20%26quot%3BThe%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau's%20Semi-Annual%20Report%20to%20Congress.%3Cp%3EMichael%20A.%20McCoy%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20continuing%20its%20crackdown%20on%20hidden%20fees%2C%20and%20targeting%20overdraft%20fees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20CFPB%20is%20proposing%20a%20rule%20to%20close%20a%20loophole%20that%20exempts%20those%20fees%20from%20certain%20standards.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInstead%2C%20the%20CFPB%20wants%20fees%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%20%243%20for%20Americans%20who%20overdraft.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETrying%20to%20buy%20something%20without%20enough%20money%20in%20your%20checking%20account%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20hefty%20surprise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Foverdraft-fees-what-banks-charge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoverdraft%20fee%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20the%20Biden%20administration%20gets%20its%20way%2C%20those%20fees%2C%20which%20produce%20major%20profits%20for%20banks%2C%20could%20soon%20shrink%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20released%20its%20proposal%20for%20a%20new%20rule%20that%20would%20protect%20Americans%20from%20the%20consequences%20of%20overdraft%20fees%20by%20ensuring%20big%20banks%20%E2%80%94%20with%20over%20%2410%20billion%20in%20assets%20%E2%80%94%20are%20complying%20with%20consumer%20law.%20That%20limit%20covers%20about%20175%20of%20the%20largest%20banks%20in%20the%20country%2C%20per%20the%20CFPB.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20are%20hit%20with%20overdraft%20fees%20when%20they%20withdraw%20more%20money%20from%20their%20accounts%20than%20what%20they%20have%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20rule%20would%20close%20a%20loophole%20that%20exempts%20some%20banks'%20overdraft%20practices%20from%20provisions%20in%20the%20Truth%20in%20Lending%20Act%2C%20which%20was%20first%20passed%20in%201968%20to%20prevent%20consumers%20from%20unfair%20billing%20practices.%20While%20the%20banks%20would%20still%20be%20able%20to%20offer%20consumer%20overdraft%20loans%20under%20the%20new%20rule%2C%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bestablish%20clear%20bright%20lines%20and%20ensure%20customers%20know%20what%20they%20are%20getting%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20overdraft%20loans%2C%26quot%3B%20CFPB%20Director%20Rohit%20Chopra%20told%20reporters%20on%20a%20Tuesday%20press%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDecades%20ago%2C%20overdraft%20loans%20got%20special%20treatment%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20banks%20to%20cover%20paper%20checks%20that%20were%20often%20sent%20through%20the%20mail%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopra%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BToday%2C%20we%20are%20proposing%20rules%20to%20close%20a%20longstanding%20loophole%20that%20allowed%20many%20large%20banks%20to%20transform%20overdraft%20into%20a%20massive%20junk%20fee%20harvesting%20machine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CFPB's%20fact%20sheet%2C%20the%20rule%20could%20save%20consumers%20%243.5%20billion%20in%20fees%20a%20year%2C%20or%20an%20average%20of%20%24150%20for%20each%20of%20the%2023%20million%20households%20who%20pay%20overdraft%20fees%20in%20any%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20CFPB%20would%20create%20standards%20for%20how%20much%20banks%20can%20charge.%20One%20of%20the%20options%20on%20the%20table%20is%20having%20banks%20charge%20just%20what%20they%20need%20to%20break%20even%3B%20the%20other%20is%20through%20using%20a%20benchmark%20fee%2C%20which%20the%20CFPB%20proposes%20could%20be%20%243%2C%20%246%2C%20%247%2C%20or%20%2414.%20The%20CFPB%20will%20be%20taking%20comments%20on%20the%20rule%20until%20April%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverdraft%20fees%20often%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20for%20consumers%2C%20and%20many%20may%20have%20had%20credit%20available%20to%20cover%20a%20purchase%20without%20going%20into%20the%20red%20on%20their%20checking%20accounts.%20A%20December%202023%20CFPB%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fnewsroom%2Fcfpb-issues-report-showing-many-americans-are-surprised-by-overdraft-fees%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20just%2022%25%20of%20consumers%20who%20were%20charged%20an%20overdraft%20fee%20in%20the%20past%20year%20expected%20to%20receive%20the%20charge%20%E2%80%94%20and%2043%25%20were%20surprised%20by%20the%20overdraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20those%20hit%20by%20overdraft%20fees%20are%20often%20already%20financially%20vulnerable%3A%20Per%20that%20CFPB%20report%2C%2081%25%20of%20consumers%20who%20frequently%20overdraft%20say%20that%20they%20had%20difficulty%20paying%20a%20bill%20at%20least%20once%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20Overdraft%20fees%20can%20also%20be%20big%20business%20for%20banks%3A%20A%20paper%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fpublications%2Fregional-economist%2F2023%2Fmar%2Fis-era-overdraft-fees-over%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCollecting%2520overdraft%2520fees%2520has%2520proved%2Cincome%2520exceeding%252020%2525%2520of%2520earnings.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20several%20major%20banks%20raked%20in%20over%20%241%20billion%20a%20year%20in%20overdraft%20fee%20income%3B%20however%2C%20overdraft%20fee%20revenue%20has%20fallen%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20especially%20as%20regulators%20like%20the%20CFPB%20have%20taken%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20long%20been%20holding%20junk%20fees%20under%20scrutiny%20for%20taking%20advantage%20of%20American%20consumers.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20in%20December%20announced%20it%20had%20finalized%20a%20new%20rule%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcar-shopping-hidden-junk-fees-scams-ftc-save-billions-time-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecould%20save%20Americans%20%243.4%20billion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20requiring%20car%20dealers%20to%20be%20upfront%20about%20the%20prices%20they%20charge%2C%20including%20discounts%20and%20add-ons.%20And%20the%20Biden%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-biden-banning-junk-fees-hidden-costs-plane-concert-tickets-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehas%20moved%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20completely%20ban%20the%20hidden%20fees%20that%20pop%20up%20w