_campaign%3DGL_asia_daily%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_source%3DNA_newsletter%26utm_content%3Darticle_link%26del_type%3D1%26pub_date%3D20240117123000%26seq_num%3D3%26si%3D611108%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Nikkei%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeijing's%20real%20nightmare%20scenario%20is%20not%20necessarily%20watching%20Lai%20Ching-te%20winning%20the%20presidency%20of%20Taiwan%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20combination%20of%20Lai%20Ching-te%20and%20perhaps%20Donald%20Trump%20coming%20back%20into%20the%20White%20House%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniels%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20would%20see%20%26quot%3Bboth%20Lai%20and%20Trump%20as%20unpredictable%20to%20Beijing's%20use%20of%20power%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20source%20of%20worry%20for%20China%20is%20if%20former%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Mike%20Pompeo%20returns%20in%20a%20leading%20position%20to%20a%20second%20Trump%20administration%2C%20Daniels%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPompeo%20has%20been%20vocal%20about%20US%20support%20for%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fus-should-recognise-taiwan-former-top-diplomat-pompeo-says-2022-03-04%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bsovereign%20country%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20a%20major%20red%20line%20for%20China%20even%20before%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping's%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20China%2C%20%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20completely%20unreliable%20as%20an%20ally%20or%20an%20opponent%2C%26quot%3B%20Stanley%20Rosen%2C%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20and%20international%20relations%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California's%20US-China%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20thus%20still%20unclear%20how%20exactly%20a%20second%20Trump%20presidency%20might%20play%20out%20for%20Beijing%2C%20Rosen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20very%20popular%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20Hong%20Kong