t%20was%20tantamount%20to%20walking%20a%20political%20tightrope.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Movement%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprde.upress.virginia.edu%2Fconversations%2F4002519%5C%22%3Ea%20great%20supporter%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20US%20President%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%2C%20who%20signed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.archives.gov%2Fpublications%2Fprologue%2F2004%2Fsummer%2Fcivil-rights-act%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DOn%2520the%2520same%2520day%2520President%2CVoting%2520Rights%2520Act%2520of%25201965.%5C%22%3ECivil%20Rights%20Act%20of%201964%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkinginstitute.stanford.edu%2Fvoting-rights-act-1965%5C%22%3EVoting%20Rights%20Act%20of%201965%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20LBJ%20was%20also%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fmoyers%2Fjournal%2F11202009%2Fprofile.html%5C%22%3Eescalation%20of%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20many%20believed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F5505453%2Fmartin-luther-king-beyond-vietnam%2F%5C%22%3EKing%E2%80%99s%20anti-war%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20and%20would%20be%20used%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%E2%80%99s%20hypocrisy%20in%20supporting%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20was%20not%20lost%20on%20King.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201965%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.digitalhistory.uh.edu%2Factive_learning%2Fexplorations%2Fvietnam%2Fvietnam_pubopinion.cfm%5C%22%3E61%25%20of%20Americans%20supported%3C%2Fa%3E%20US%20military%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20King%20was%20asking%20hard%20questions%20about%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20wartime%20decision-making%20and%20unmet%20promises%20of%20social%20uplift%20through%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F09%2F22%2Fopinion%2Fvietnam-war-great-society.html%5C%22%3EGreat%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%20programs.%20King%20wondered%20how%20a%20nation%20could%20drop%20tons%20of%20bombs%20and%20napalm%20on%20civilians%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkinginstitute.stanford.edu%2Fvietnam-war%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DIn%2520his%2520last%2520Sunday%2520sermon%2CRemaining%2520Awake%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520219%5C%22%3Ethe%20name%20of%20peace%20and%20freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20violently%20subjugating%20its%20own%20Black%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20could%20a%20nation%20spend%20so%20much%20money%20on%20a%20war%2C%20King%20asked%2C%20when%20it%20could%20not%20feed%20or%20protect%20its%20own%20people%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20promises%20of%20the%20Great%20Society%20have%20been%20shot%20down%20on%20the%20battlefield%20of%20Vietnam%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aavw.org%2Fspecial_features%2Fspeeches_speech_king02.html%5C%22%3EKing%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20speech%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%20on%20February%2025%2C%201967.%20%E2%80%9CBillions%20are%20liberally%20expended%20for%20this%20ill-considered%20war.%20The%20security%20we%20profess%20to%20seek%20in%20foreign%20adventures%20we%20will%20lose%20in%20our%20decaying%20cities.%20The%20bombs%20in%20Vietnam%20explode%20at%20home.%20They%20destroy%20the%20hopes%20and%20possibilities%20for%20a%20decent%20America.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fgwmp%2Flearn%2Fhistoryculture%2Flbjandmlk.htm%5C%22%3EJohnson%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20argued%20that%20military%20force%20was%20essential%20to%20protect%20South%20Vietnam%20from%20the%20encroachment%20of%20communism%20from%20the%20north.%20As%20Johnson%20saw%20it%2C%20North%20Vietnam%20and%20its%20National%20Liberation%20Front%20were%20a%20threat%20to%20democracy%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKing%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thirteen.org%2Fblog-post%2Fmartin-luther-kings-most-controversial-speech-beyond-vietnam%2F%5C%22%3Eadvisers%20pleaded%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20him%20not%20to%20speak%20out%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20political%20costs%20would%20be%20too%20high.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20they%20reminded%20King%20that%20there%20was%20more%20than%20enough%20work%20to%20do%20in%20the%20U.S.%20to%20end%20poverty%20and%20secure%20equal%20rights%20for%20Black%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20King%20ultimately%20broke%20with%20his%20advisers%20and%20President%20Johnson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%201967%2C%20King%20followed%20the%20lead%20of%20his%20wife%20%E2%80%93%20and%20anti-war%20activist%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F2018%2F02%2Fcoretta-scott-king%2F552557%2F%5C%22%3ECoretta%20Scott%20King%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20began%20speaking%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%201967%2C%20King%20led%20his%20first%20anti-war%20march%20in%20Chicago.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jofreeman.com%2Fphotos%2FKingAtChicago.html%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20called%20on%20peace%20activists%20to%20organize%20%E2%80%9Cas%20effectively%20as%20the%20war%20hawks.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20month%20later%2C%20on%20April%204%2C%201967%2C%20King%20gave%20the%20speech%20at%20the%20Riverside%20Church%20in%20New%20York%20City%20that%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20the%20last%20year%20of%20his%20life%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanrhetoric.com%2Fspeeches%2Fmlkatimetobreaksilence.htm%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CBeyond%20Vietnam%20%E2%88%92%20A%20Time%20to%20Break%20the%20Silence%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%20In%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkinginstitute.stanford.edu%2Fencyclopedia%2Fbeyond-vietnam%5C%22%3Erevolutionary%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20King%20described%20how%20he%20was%20morally%20compelled%20to%20speak%20out%20against%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20and%20weeks%20after%2C%20he%20would%20lose%20masses%20of%20supporters%2C%20Black%20and%20white%20alike.%20He%20lost%20hard-earned%20political%20allies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkinginstitute.stanford.edu%2Fjohnson-ly