rica%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKing%20had%20no%20regrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20understood%20the%20difficulty%20of%20speaking%20out%20against%20the%20war.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20when%20pressed%20by%20the%20demands%20of%20inner%20truth%2C%20men%20do%20not%20easily%20assume%20the%20task%20of%20opposing%20their%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%2C%20especially%20in%20time%20of%20war%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20King%2C%20a%20preacher%20at%20heart%2C%20silence%20had%20become%20betrayal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20the%20US%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20greatest%20purveyor%20of%20violence%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20King%20said%20the%20soul%20of%20America%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20never%20be%20saved%20so%20long%20as%20it%20destroys%20the%20deepest%20hopes%20of%20men%20the%20world%20over.%E2%80%9D%20He%20warned%20that%20America%20had%20lost%20moral%20authority%20abroad%20and%20derided%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20deadly%20Western%20arrogance%20that%20has%20poisoned%20the%20international%20atmosphere%20for%20so%20long.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKing%20pointed%20to%20the%20role%20of%20the%20US%20in%20prohibiting%20the%20realisation%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20revolutionary%20government%20seeking%20self-determination%E2%80%9D%20in%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20poignantly%20in%20that%201967%20speech%20at%20Riverside%20Church%2C%20King%20detailed%20the%20devastating%20costs%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20and%20described%20the%20millions%20of%20children%20and%20women%20who%20were%20killed%20by%20American%20bombs%20and%20bullets%20and%20the%20poor%20masses%20who%20were%20spared%20slaughter%20only%20to%20face%20a%20slow%2C%20painful%20death%20by%20disease%20and%20starvation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20King%20turned%20to%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cenemy%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20North%20Vietnamese.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20we%20do%20not%20condone%20their%20actions%2C%E2%80%9D%20King%20said%20in%20the%20speech%2C%20%E2%80%9Csurely%20we%20must%20see%20that%20the%20men%20we%20supported%20pressed%20t