edia%20platforms.%20The%20plaintiffs%20claim%20that%20Dhoni's%20statements%20and%20allegations%20have%20harmed%20their%20image.%20The%20defamation%20plea%20is%20scheduled%20for%20a%20hearing%20on%20January%2018%20before%20Justice%20Prathiba%20M%20Singh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Foff-the-field%2Fdefamation-suit-filed-against-ms-dhoni-by-former-business-partners%2Farticleshow%2F106919205.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Court%20Relief%20For%20Goa%20Students%20Barred%20From%20Exam%20For%20Stealing%20Chips%2C%20Pens%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Goa%20bench%20of%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20has%20directed%20two%20engineering%20students%20to%20do%20community%20service%20for%20two%20hours%20daily%20for%20two%20months%2C%20giving%20them%20relief%20from%20strict%20action%20by%20their%20college%20after%20they%20apparently%20stole%20items%20like%20potato%20chips%2C%20chocolates%2C%20pens%20during%20a%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20comprising%20Justice%20Devendra%20Kumar%20Upadhyay%20and%20Justice%20MS%20Sonak%20on%20Monday%20set%20aside%20the%20decision%20of%20Birla%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20and%20Science%20(BITS)%20Pilani%2C%20Goa%20campus%2C%20to%20debar%20the%20students%20from%20appearing%20for%20their%20semester%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20instead%20directed%20the%20students%2C%20both%20aged%2018%2C%20to%20perform%20community%20service%20for%20two%20hours%20every%20day%20at%20an%20old-age%20home%20in%20Goa%20for%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20court%20order%2C%20five%20students%2C%20including%20the%20two%20petitioners%2C%20were%20alleged%20to%20have%20stolen%20potato%20chips%2C%20chocolates%2C%20sanitisers%2C%20pens%2C%20notepads%2C%20cellphone%20stands%2C%20two%20desk%20lamps%2C%20and%20three%20Bluetooth%20speakers%20from%20stalls%20during%20a%20conference%20on%20the%20college%20campus%20in%20November%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20caught%2C%20the%20students%20had%20claimed%20that%20they%20were%20under%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20items%20were%20abandoned%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20case%20papers%2C%20the%20students%20returned%20the%20items%20and%20apologised%20in%20writing%20for%20their%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20standing%20panel%20of%20the%20institute%20had%20debarred%20all%20five%20students%20from%20registration%20for%20three%20semesters%20while%20imposing%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20on%20each%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20challenged%20the%20decision%20before%20the%20director%20of%20the%20institution%20who%20revoked%20the%20cancellation%20of%20semesters%20for%20three%20students%20but%20maintained%20the%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20two%20other%20students%2C%20the%20director%20maintained%20the%20Rs%2050%2C000%20fine%20and%20said%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20allowed%20to%20take%20exams%20during%20semester%20one%20(2023-24).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20then%20approached%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20students'%20petitions%2C%20the%20HC%20deferred%20its%20decision%20on%20two%20occasions%20to%20enable%20the%20BITS%20director%20to%20reconsider%20the%20punishment%20of%20cancellation%20of%20the%20semester.%20But%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20final%20order%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20HC%20said%20it%20got%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20director%20was%20irked%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20students%20had%20dared%20to%20seek%20court%20intervention%20against%20his%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20said%20that%20though%20they%20were%20hurt%20by%20this%20approach%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bdirector%20of%20an%20Institute%20of%20Eminence%26quot%3B%2C%20they%20have%20refrained%20from%20saying%20anything%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...%20we%20are%20mindful%20that%20the%20two%20petitioners%20before%20us%20have%20to%20complete%20their%20education%20with%20the%20respondents%20for%20the%20next%20few%20years%20and%20not%20be%20scarred%20for%20life%20due%20to%20indiscretion%20or%20even%20indiscipline%20indulged%20by%20them%20on%20this%20one%20occasion%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20in%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20said%20that%20ordinarily%2C%20courts%20must%20be%20slow%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20internal%20affairs%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Buniversity%2C%20particularly%20on%20issues%20concerning%20disciplinary%20proceedings%20against%20students%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20said%20an%20institute%20cannot%20claim%20immunity%20on%20the%20principle%20that%20courts%20should%20be%20slow%20in%20interfering%20in%20such%20matters%20if%20it%20acts%20contrary%20to%20its%20own%20guidelines%2C%20ignores%20UGC%20(University%20Grants%20Commission)%20directives%2C%20discriminates%20between%20two%20sets%20of%20students%20and%20%26quot%3Bbreaches%20the%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice%20and%20fair%20play%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B..When%20it%20is%20found%20that%20there%20is%20discrimination%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20imposition%20of%20penalties%20or%2C%20where%20the%20penalties%20imposed%20are%20in%20breach%20of%20guidelines%20enacted%20by%20the%20Institute%20itself%20or%20where%20the%20penalty%20imposed%20excludes%20considerations%20of%20reformation%2C%20the%20Institute%20cannot%20claim%20any%20immunity%20from%20judicial%20review%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20there%20is%20not%20much%20material%20as%20such%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20role%20played%20by%20the%20petitioners%20and%20the%20other%20three%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20accepting%20the%20institute's%20case%20that%20there%20was%20some%20difference%2C%20this%20is%20a%20fit%20case%20where%20the%20petitioners%2C%20in%20addition%20t