ed%20by%20Patriot%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20to%20have%20simply%20missed%20its%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22829%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20sapper%20recovers%20the%20warhead%20of%20a%20Kinzhal%20missile.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a64ffd43bb77284b9d39af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221036%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20sapper%20recovers%20the%20warhead%20of%20a%20Kinzhal%20missile.%3Cp%3EState%20Emergency%20Service%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20more%20and%20more%20evidence%20showing%20that%20what%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine%20say%20on%20this%20matter%20is%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chinese%20defense%20analyst%20Yin%20Jie%20wrote%20in%20November%20in%20the%20Shaanxi%20military%20magazine%20Ordnance%20Industry%20Science%20and%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20such%20journals%20don't%20necessarily%20reflect%20views%20or%20intel%20from%20within%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%2C%20state%20agencies%20must%20approve%20their%20publishers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20Yin%20issued%20a%20surprisingly%20critical%20review%20of%20how%20Russia%20uses%20the%20Kinzhal%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BDagger%2C%26quot%3B%20writing%20that%20the%20missile%20was%20%26quot%3Bunlikely%20to%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20directly%20contradicts%20how%20Russia%2C%20a%20close%20ally%20of%20China%2C%20has%20portrayed%20the%20weapon%20as%20a%20pivotal%20munition%20for%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20'short-term%2C%20hasty%20project'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20analyst%20spelled%20out%20various%20ways%20Russia%20had%20undermined%20its%20own%20missile%2C%20such%20as%20how%20the%20Kinzhal%20had%20been%20fired%20and%20its%20availability.%20The%20Kinzhal%2C%20they%20concluded%2C%20just%20wasn't%20the%20star%20that%20Moscow%20made%20it%20out%20to%2